<br>
&quot;No, We shouldn't ask her to send anyone else. Doing such may cause havoc. The men will know who we are then, and fighting may break out. We don't want that. If we're discovered, it will only be us. We can't let the men know we are Amazons. Calling in Athelfi will tell them that. Our escape, if needed, must depends solely on us. The rafts will take us past Themiscrya if we are forced to use them, making the men think we've come from farther down the riverbank, a different part of the land. When we dock the raft, we can destroy the one we used. We'll then weave our way through the land, in case they've sent scouts after us. We can confuse them with fake trails heading south of the village, then take to the trees when the time comes and return to the village that way.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Satisfied with that, she looked to Dawn to see if she agreed::  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#993300>(7/9/01 12:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=239.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gargarensia Village </span><hr size=1>  Dawn nodded, agreeing with the plan.<br>
